        "id": 261557,
        "name": "Sam",
        "username": "scoupland",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/scoupland/{size}/50708_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-02-19T04:10:58.146Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I would like to see more privacy controls over who can contact me on the app, primary other members of a group that I donâ€™t have contact details for.</p>\n<p>Currently, anyone from a group I join can directly message me even though I will not always know who they are.</p>\n<p>As a use case, when safeguarding under 18-year-olds on the app, they canâ€™t be added to a group with other members that have not been DBS checked (UK police check) because anyone in that group can message that underage person.</p>\n<p>Even the strictest privacy settings where you limit who can contact you, does not apply to contacts in groups (i.e. you technically have an existing chat with them, so they can message you)</p>\n<p>Please could we have a privacy setting that could help with safeguarding under 18 years using the app and increase privacy for groups members, a few privacy options could be:</p>\n<p>As a user, only I can initiate a chat<br>\nor<br>\nAs a user, no unknown users from a group can message me<br>\nor<br>\nAs a group admin, I can switch off group members being able to message other unknown members in the group</p>\n<p>I would greatly appreciate this being considered.</p>\n<p>Many thanks<br>\nSam</p>",
